description:
The Insurance Institute for Highway Safety (IIHS) is an independent, nonprofit scientific and educational organization dedicated to reducing deaths, injuries and property damage from motor vehicle crashes through research and evaluation and through education of consumers, policymakers and safety professionals.

The Highway Loss Data Institute (HLDI) shares and supports this mission through scientific studies of insurance data representing the human and economic losses resulting from the ownership and operation of different types of vehicles and by publishing insurance loss results by vehicle make and model.

Both organizations are wholly supported by  auto insurers and insurance associations.

IIHS runs vehicle crash tests and other evaluations at our state-of-the-art Vehicle Research Center. Consumers can use IIHS crash test, crash avoidance, and headlight ratings to compare vehicles when shopping for the safest car, minivan, SUV, or pickup truck.

description:
Three Themes

I am an amateur filmmaker. I try and take a camera everywhere I go. Through this channel I aim to work around the following three principals.

I. Testing equipment for educational purposes. I rely heavily on youtube to make informed decisions on audio/video equipment purchases. I continually test audio/video equipment and at times will share that via youtune. I generally purchase older or discounted equipment and hope my testing videos will assist others in their own endeavors.

II. Music... It's my greatest love and passion. Anything related to music that I hope others may enjoy will find its way onto this channel.

III. DIY projects. At times I will document, via video or photo, projects that I build or design to save money.

description:
「ぼくたちにとって動いて見えるテレビ映像ですら、昆虫から見ればカタカタとした 動きにしか見えない。時間とはいったい何だろうか？」
時間を引きのばして昆虫の世界を見れば、そこには驚異の世界が見えてくる。私たちがスムーズに見えるテレビもカマキリが見たらコマ落としの映像にしかみえないだろう。（なにしろ獲物を捕る速度はわずか1/20秒である）
それほど昆虫の動きは早い。普通のビデオカメラではとらえきれない昆虫の動きや行動を高速度ビデオカメラを用いて時間を10倍から40倍に引き延ばして撮影している。
今では動画はビデオカメラだけでなくスチールカメラでも撮れる。このコーナーでは撮りだめた数々の動画や新しくスチールカメラで撮っている最新動画などを掲載していくことにする。

description: We all want to sense the world in motion around us. Quickly, accurately, in detail, and in a natural way. Without cables and complex instrumentation. A sci-fi dream in the beginning of the third millennium, when we started Inertia Technology, but now not anymore. Unprecedented recent advances in electronics miniaturization and low-power wireless communication made this vision possible. We are proud to have contributed to it. With our products, you can move your lab in the field and acquire all the sensor data wirelessly at high sampling rates.

description:
Welcome to JimLiElevators: My name is Jim and I am an elevator photographer based in central Texas. I have always loved elevators when I was a kid. Been filming since 2005. I present to you videos of elevators that are both vintage and modern. Not only that I film elevators, but I've also been interested into trains as well. I'll occasionally upload animated elevators because I've had a lot of fun making them. So with that said, I hope you enjoy your visit to my channel.

Thanks so much for your loyal viewership. I take pride in keeping this channel clean for all ages. I am also a born Christian, so I want to keep it pleasing to Jesus as well! “For God so loved the world that he gave his only son that believes in him shall not perish but have eternal life. John 3:16."

I'm also thankful to Andrew Reams (DieselDucy) who's the deepest inspiration towards me to start this channel. That said, make sure you subscribe. Thanks and have a great day! :D

description:
High Speed Interconnects (HSI) is an American company, which extrudes and assembles high-performance coaxial cable assemblies to meet your challenging electrical and mechanical requirements. HSI's low-loss, low-capacitance, phase-stable coaxial interconnect solutions are available in a variety of cable constructions including circular and micro coaxial connector terminations down to 0.3mm pitch and fine wire direct to board terminations down to 0.175 mm

Headquartered in Scottsdale, AZ, HSI is one of a few global manufacturers extruding its own high-performance coaxial cable and expanded PTFE. HSI's coaxial cable assemblies range from 16 to 52 AWG and are available in a variety of configurations such as; single coax, twinax, triax, quadax, shielded parallel pairs, shielded twisted pairs, differential pairs, and other multi-conductor solutions. HSI's assemblies are available as discrete, ribbonized, or multiconductor (bundled) constructions.

A train is alive with things that should be seen and heard. It’s a living, breathing something — you just have to want to learn its rhythm.

description:
Hallo Science Fan! 
Mikroskopisches Filmen ist faszinierend, knifflig, spannend und schwierig. 
Bei ScienceFilm nutzen wir die ganze Welt der Mikroskopie um neue Einblicke in Science und Technology zu gewinnen.
Du kannst unsere Filme:
- kaufen, als Footage für Deinen eigenen Film
- bestellen, um schöne Bilder aus der Natur, Life Science oder Technik zu erhalten
- produzieren lassen, um damit analytische Fragestellungen für Deine Produktion / Industrie / Forschung&Entwicklung zu lösen.
Wir bieten Highspeed-Filming, Mikroskop-Film, Oberflächen-Mikroskopie & Animation für Dein Projekt.
go for it!
andre.kempe@sciencefilm.de

channelName: The Frank-Ratchye STUDIO for Creative Inquiry
description:
The Frank-Ratchye STUDIO for Creative Inquiry is a flexible laboratory for new modes of arts research, production and presentation. Founded in 1989 within the College of Fine Arts at Carnegie Mellon University (CMU), the STUDIO serves as a locus for hybrid enterprises on the CMU campus, the Pittsburgh region, and internationally. Our current emphasis on new-media arts builds on more than two decades of experience hosting interdisciplinary artists in an environment enriched by world-class science and engineering departments. Through our residencies and outreach programs, the STUDIO provides opportunities for learning, dialogue and research that lead to innovative breakthroughs, new policies, and the redefinition of the role of artists in a quickly changing world.

To learn more, visit http://studioforcreativeinquiry.org/

description:
Canyon Run Videos & Photography is located in Southern California. We began operating in 2010 producing multiple camera auto racing videos. Our YouTube channel (youtube.com/c/CanyonRunVideos) has well over 500 videos online. A few years later we built our first drone that came in a kit where every component was à la carte. The complete build ended up costing nearly $4,000 and weighed nearly five pounds including a pilot's camera  and a a GoPro camera as well. These days we fly the DJI Mavic 2 Pro with all of the bells and whistles. We received our FAA Part 107 Certificate in 2021 and we really enjoy shooting aerial video and photography. We also offer hand held photography, or our DJI RONIN RS3 Pro gimble video rig.  

Please take a look at some of our past work for yourself and if you like what you see then let's talk about your aerial project if you like.

(old, see update below) At the moment this is almost entirely Planetside 2 footage - as that's about the only game I play lately.  This footage is recorded originally @ 60fps / 1080p using shadowplay, and then compressed into x264 / 30fps and uploaded here. No voice comms is recorded, only what comes out of the speakers.   Since dropping the shadowplay buffer from 20 minutes to 10 minutes I seem to not have stuttering issues - interesting.

Update: 4k footage, 20 minute buffer again, I'll record voice comms, because after 10 years of not recording voices, I think that was a bad idea.  *shrug*. I'm also playing games other than Planetside 2, lately - although that is still my favourite game

Contemporary R&B vocals blended with hip-hop flows, the actor/singer/songwriter/producer debuted on the scene with his smash hit “Gotta Make It” in 2005. Within the first decade of his career, he released five albums that peaked within the Top 20 of the Billboard 200 chart, including "Ready", "Pain Passion & Pleasure," "Chapter V," and "Trigga" as well as 15 solo singles that hit the Top Ten of the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop chart. 

Songz’s top hits include platinum “Na Na”,  platinum “Say Ahh”,  RIAA-certified “Bottoms Up” featuring Nicki Minaj, gold “2 Reasons” featuring T.I., platinum “Slow Motion” and as well as platinum “Heart Attack."  Songz lends his soulful vocals on featured hits from Twista’s "Girl Tonight" to J. Cole’s “Can’t Get Enough."

description:
Jamaican singer, musician, songwriter, and activist Bob Marley has served as a world ambassador for reggae music and sold more than 20 million records throughout his career—making him the first international superstar to emerge from the so-called Third World.

Bob Marley was posthumously inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 1994; in December 1999, his 1977 album “Exodus” was named Album of the Century by Time Magazine and his song “One Love” was designated Song of the Millennium by the BBC. Since its release in 1984, Marley’s “Legend” compilation has annually sold over 250,000 copies according to Nielsen Sound Scan, and it is only the 17th album to exceed sales of 10 million copies since SoundScan began its tabulations in 1991. It currently sits as the 2nd highest-selling compilation album of all time, and the 2nd longest Billboard-charting album in history.

Today, Bob Marley is known throughout the world for his message of unity, love, self-determination, and RASTAFARI.

description:
Before television, people came to movie theatres to watch the news. British Pathé was at the forefront of cinematic journalism, blending information with entertainment to popular effect. Over the course of a century, it documented everything from major armed conflicts and seismic political crises to the curious hobbies and eccentric lives of ordinary people.

Now considered to be the finest newsreel archive in the world, British Pathé is a treasure trove of 85,000 films unrivalled in their historical and cultural significance.

British Pathé also represents the Reuters historical collection, which includes more than 136,000 items from the news agencies Gaumont Graphic (1910-1932), Empire News Bulletin (1926-1930), British Paramount (1931-1957), and Gaumont British (1934-1959), as well as Visnews content from 1957 to the end of 1984. All footage can be viewed on the British Pathé website. www.britishpathe.com

We also represent SPIEGEL TV via our website.

ALL RIGHTS RESERVED

Since then, the Dynamic Fracture Laboratory has been actively developing new tools and techniques to address these issues.

description:
Joe's Arcade is a combination of my two main arcade projects, The Game Preserve and Classic Arcade Works.  

The Game Preserve is a classic arcade located in Houston, TX, owned and operated by myself and three friends.  As of May 2014 we have 90 classic arcade and pinball machine set to free play for all to enjoy.

Classic Arcade Works is my company that focuses on the restoration of classic arcade machines with a heavy emphasis in new cabinet construction.  As of May 2014 I am not taking orders for new cabinets, but still offer restoration services and some original replacement parts.

description:
The demolition of a large high-rise hotel in San Francisco with time-lapses and closeups.  Plus a few other demolition videos.

The Jack Tar Hotel (aka Cathedral Hill Hotel) was completed in 1960 and occupied an entire city block of San Francisco. After over 50 years, it has been demolished to make way for the construction of a new hospital.

After the demolition of the hotel completed, this channel went idle for years. It became active again briefly for the demolition of an old TV studio building, but that's now complete as well, so the channel is idle again.  Should I have access to another demolition project, it is possible that uploads could resume again someday, but I see no sign of that for now.

If you'd like to follow the construction of the new hospital, or of the building that follows the TV studio demolition, check out my separate "Hospital Construction" channel.

description:
Caving, Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends, Garden Railway & Meccano
Mainly videos of caves and abandoned mines in England and Wales.  A cornucopia of material for armchair cavers.

What is Caving?
Caving is an adventure activity full of physical challenges and an outlet for a real explorer’s spirit, not to mention a great way to keep fit.
It is an experience of nature unlike any other - not just close to nature but within nature itself.
The experience is incredibly rewarding where magical sights, thousands of years in the making, sculpted rocks and the delicate formations are a joy to behold.
For more information about caving and how to start go to https://newtocaving.com.

If you don't like caving for any reason then there's always the Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends Garden Railway or the Meccano videos to watch.

All photos on this site by Brendan Marris.

#thomasandfriends #thomasthetankengine #thomasthetankengineandfriends #thomasthetank #thomasthetrain

description:
I have an absolute obsession with cameras. If a day goes by where I don't pick up a camera and shoot some photos or film something I feel off. To that end, I often end up shooting stuff just for the sake of creation. Eventually I realized I wanted a place to put some of this stuff, so I can easily share it, and to know it is backed up somewhere - even if just on youtube. 

In essence this channel works as a film-makers laboratory. Dumb Ideas, experiments, camera tests, practice films as well as things I felt like were worth documenting and everything in between. Some of it is really old. Some of it is new. There's no real rhyme or reason happening.

description:
Pink Floyd, one of the most successful and influential groups ever, formed in the 1960s when Roger Waters, Nick Mason and Richard Wright were studying at college in London. They added Roger ‘Syd’ Barrett, a Cambridge friend, who named the band after bluesmen Pink Anderson and Floyd Council.
 
Debut album The Piper At The Gates Of Dawn is still considered one of the greatest psychedelic albums, but in 1968 Syd Barrett’s erratic behaviour prompted his replacement by David Gilmour, another friend. Pink Floyd developed the members’ compositional and improvisational talents, and built a large audience via many live tours, releasing a succession of hit albums, including The Dark Side Of The Moon, Wish You Were Here, and The Wall.
 
Roger Waters left in 1985, but the band enjoyed continuing success with the studio albums A Momentary Lapse Of Reason and The Division Bell, accompanied by world tours. The final Pink Floyd release was 2014’s The Endless River, another worldwide #1 album.
